{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN2/uttara-sutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>At Rājagaha. Standing to one side, the god Uttara recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“This life, so very short, is led onward. <br>\nThere’s no shelter for one led on by old age. <br>\nSeeing this peril in death, <br>\ndo good deeds that bring happiness.” <br>\n<br>\n“This life, so very short, is led onward. <br>\nThere’s no shelter for one led on by old age. <br>\nSeeing this peril in death, <br>\na seeker of peace would drop the world’s bait.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN2/anathapindika-sutta/\">SN.2.20. Anāthapiṇḍika Sutta (“With Anāthapiṇḍika”)</a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At Rājagaha. Standing to one side, the god Uttara recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“This life, so very short, is led onward. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nThere’s no shelter for one led on by old age. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nSeeing this peril in death, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\ndo good deeds that bring happiness.” "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n“This life, so very short, is led onward. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","pro